{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"de02ab7c-693a-4314-aec8-8591203a1a57","content":"The directory doesn't exist yet, but I can tell you exactly what you need to configure in your `.csproj` to publish as a dotnet tool:\n\n### Required `.csproj` properties\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Makes it a dotnet tool -->\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n\n  <!-- The command users will run (e.g., `dotnet tool install -g my-mcp-server`) -->\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- NuGet metadata -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server for ...</Description>\n  <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/you/MyMcpServer</PackageProjectUrl>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n\n  <!-- Must be a console app -->\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Key points\n\n1. **`PackAsTool=true`** — this is the critical property that makes it installable via `dotnet tool install`.\n2. **`ToolCommandName`** — the CLI command name users invoke.\n3. **`OutputType` must be `Exe`** — required for stdio transport.\n\n### Publish steps\n\n```bash\n# Pack\ndotnet pack -c Release\n\n# Push to NuGet.org (get API key from nuget.org/account/apikeys)\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_API_KEY \\\n  --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Users install with\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server   # runs via stdio\n```\n\nWould you like me to create the project or modify an existing `.csproj`?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"621ac0d4-31f0-409b-85be-03070baab808","outputTokens":494,"requestId":"502C:CE842:D577F7:F5C502:69F2ABC6"},"id":"98b8f312-7b42-47ce-9612-f80c1afaddb7","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:09:35.610Z","parentId":"d098a3ff-58d9-4d49-bec4-d088e0f14241"}
